items.name: Haydee
items.description:
It's everyone's favorite android-thing, Haydee!

This is a lora trained on 136 hand picked images of Haydee from... Haydee. There are no 3d/sfm images included, it's exclusively digital art. It handles her features pretty well, and can do most angles you can think of and usually gets the mechanical arms and head right. It was trained on danbooru-style tags, so use those when trying to prompt - I've included the tags in a .txt file in the "Training Images" download below.

It works pretty well with most ckpts, but I recommend Anything 4.5, I used it for most of the example images.

NOTES:

-The helmet and the thing around her neck is virtually unremovable, even if prompting nudity. It also seems impervious to trying to make it a different color, although the leotard she wears is easier to change colors.

-It can do a "male" Haydee pretty easily, too. See last example image.

- It can kind of do the handgun from the game, however the results can vary.

Example prompt: (See example images, most images still have their metadata. Just drag the images onto the PNG info tab and import it.)

Thanks, and have fun!

items.name: Melusine
items.description:
UPDATE: Model V3 is a retraining of the model with a higher-quality data set, more careful tag pruning and more steps, with the end result more closely resembling the original comic artwork at 0.8-1.0 weight at Clip Skip 2. Requires more weight adjustment than V2 to play nice with other LoRAs as a result, though. Again, if you're having trouble with the outfit, add the positive tags witch hat, orange hair, long hair, aqua dress, black turtleneck, long sleeves, black pantyhose to ensure you get her default look. This version also tends to make her hair very long, so add very long hair and extremely long hair to the negatives if you're having trouble with that.

--

Based on the main character of the Belgian comic series of the same name. Trained on Anything 4.5 with anime.vae, using 70 pieces of art from the original artist, as well as a few pieces of fanart to fill some gaps.

Works well at 1.0 weight, but might require some adjustment depending on what other LoRAs you use with it, some get overpowered by the thick lines inherent to this one. If you're having trouble with the outfit, add the positive tags witch hat, orange hair, long hair, aqua dress, black turtleneck, long sleeves, black pantyhose to ensure you get her default look.

items.name: pepe_frog
items.description:
https://t.me/stdif_kos

Pepe the Frog (/ˈpɛpeɪ/) is a cartoon character and Internet meme created by cartoonist Matt Furie. Designed as a green anthropomorphic frog with a humanoid body, Pepe originated in Furie's 2005 comic Boy's Club.[2] The character became an Internet meme when his popularity steadily grew across websites such as Myspace, Gaia Online, and 4chan in 2008. By 2015, he had become one of the most popular memes used on 4chan and Tumblr.[3] Different types of Pepe memes include "Sad Frog", "Smug Frog", "Angry Pepe", "Feels Frog", and "You will never..." Frog. Since 2014, 'rare Pepes' have been posted on the 'meme market' as if they were trading cards.[4][5][6]

Originally an apolitical character, Pepe was appropriated from 2015 to 2016 onward as a symbol of the alt-right movement.[7][8][9] The Anti-Defamation League included Pepe in its hate symbol database in 2016, but said most instances of Pepe were not used in a hate-related context.[10][11] Since then, Furie has expressed his dismay at Pepe being used as a hate symbol and has sued organizations for doing so.[12]

In 2019, Pepe was used by protesters in the 2019–2020 Hong Kong protests. Despite being used in a political context, Pepe the Frog's use in Hong Kong is not perceived as being connected with alt-right ideology. Furie has welcomed the use of Pepe by Hong Kong protesters.

Pepe remains a recognizable and familiar sight on social media platforms such as 4chan, Twitch, Reddit, and Discord, where images are modified into custom Pepe-based emoji.

items.name: Kendoll Boots 肯豆靴
items.description:
It's A lora trained for fashion style boots designed by Alexander.Wang. and became popular in China 1~2 years ago. I don't know why it is called 'Kendoll Boots', maybe Kendoll wears it and Kendoll is a famous model?

Nevermind.

It's the first lora I made. So it remains a lot to improve with.

Feel free to do some improvements if you want.

====================================

这个lora主要用于生成由亚历山大.王设计的一种方头款式长靴，

前几年在中国还挺流行的，我也不知道野爹生的淘宝商和营销号为什么要把它叫成“肯豆靴”，反正现在全网都在这么叫。

主要特点是能生成方鞋头，鞋头一圈银边概率出。然后靴筒部分改进挺大的。因为chilloutmix原生底模生成的thigh boots大概率像一截胶袜配高跟，没有靴筒和大腿之间的空隙感，使用这个lora可以生出比较正常的靴筒。

【Chilloutmix原生 'thigh_boots' prompt】

【使用Kendoll Lora后，明显出现的靴筒】

【碎碎念注意】除了感叹几条营销策划狗又通过造势刮所谓的“潮流风”，捷足先登地抢走某些外来好设计好思路的命名权，再通过市场营销成功洗脑了相当一部分中国人，最后裹挟着全社会的大多数都不得不叫唤它“肯豆靴”以外，其实无所谓了，我只是开心SD是开源的且还没成为商品，更开心国内没有什么劳什子代理商，永远也别有。

这是我练的第一炉丹，肯定有许多要回炉的地方。

想要改进请自取哈，别客气。

If you want to support me, then you can subscribe to my Patreon and get builds earlier than they come out here (versions on patreon will always be newer by one than here) This will help me a lot in updating the video card over time to make models even better and faster (the main thing is better)

In principle, the same techniques were used here as in my previous model, only a little better.

LORA weight from 0.2 to 1 depending on your goals, 1 - closer to the original style, there are no restrictions here. I use 0.6-0.7

just use hires fix as much as your video card is capable of, so as not to give an error, with 8gb of video memory it is 512x768 with hires fix 2, upscaler Latent (nearest-exact) or just Latent (if there are problems with the image), the picture will be much more detailed.

Trigger Words: makise kurisu

Combined with my other LORA

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

Model trained in SD 1.5 with photos generated with Midjourney, created to generate aliens, people, animals/creatures...

TOKEN : pdalns, pdalns style, pdalns style of _____, "x" mix "pdalns"

Possible positives: cute, creature, character creepy, fluffy, seamless, epic, cinematic, intricate details, award winning, great lighting, shading, high quality, detailed, digital art, trending arstation, beautiful, "x" mix "pdalns"

Possible negatives: cartoon, pencil draw, bad photo, low detail

ugly, pencil draw, bad photo, cartoon, bad colors, bad taste, illustration, low resolution, low quality, cropped, wrong, black and white, bw, out of focus, blurry....

disfigured, kitsch, ugly,oversaturated, grain, low-res, deformed, blurry, bad anatomy, disfigured, poorly drawn face, mutation, mutated, extra limb, ugly, poorly drawn hands, missing limb, blurry, floating limbs, disconnected limbs, malformed hands, blur, out of focus, long neck, long body, ugly, disgusting, poorly drawn, childish, mutilated, , mangled, old, surreal, close photo, close shot, close up, close up photo....

You can see the prompts in the images.

Improve images and increase resolution

  • Generate images and choose the one you like the most, and send it to the img2img section.

  • In img2img, choose to generate 2-4 or more images. If you want it to resemble the original photo, set "denoising" to 0.4-0.5-0.6. If you want more changes in the image, you can set "denoising" from 0.6 to 1.

  • Once those 4 images are generated, choose the one you like the most (or generate more images until you find the one you like) and send it back to img2img.

  • Now we will increase the resolution of the image. If the photo is 512x512, we can set it to 680x680 and 50 steps for example (changing "denoising" if we want it to resemble more or less) and generate 2-4 more images again and choose the one we like and send it back to img2img and keep increasing the resolution of the image little by little until you want to, in order to not lose details.

  • At this point, we can lower denoising to 0.15 if we don't want the image to change, and generate 1 image with 50/100 steps, this way we can make giant images with high resolution/quality.

ENJOY !!!!

items.name: Zundamon
items.description:
Regarding the use of characters, please check the Tohoku Zunko official guidelines. https://zunko.jp/guideline.html

Study at ACertainty.ckpt. A strength of 0.3 to 0.8 is recommended.

I think it's relatively easy to use because the clothes are simple, but you can increase the recall rate with the following prompts.

green short hair, yellow eyes, white shirt, suspender shorts,

The learning material does not have a background, so if you want a background, please specify it strongly in the prompt.

Tail hair is one of the structures that is easy to collapse. No solution has been confirmed so far.(postscript. I was informed that adding "ponytail" to the prompt might improve it. thank you.)

Depending on the model and the strength of LoRA, the breasts may become larger, or the height and age may increase, so adjust the prompt/negative prompt to your liking.

This is the first time LoRA has been released, so if you have any impressions or inadequacies, please leave a comment.

キャラクターの利用に関しては、東北ずん子公式のガイドラインを確認してください。https://zunko.jp/guideline.html

ACertainty.ckptにて学習。強度は0.3～0.8くらいが推奨。

服がシンプルなので比較的使いやすい方だと思いますが、以下のプロンプトで再現率を上げることができます。

green short hair, yellow eyes, white shirt, suspender shorts,

学習素材に背景がないので、背景がが必要な場合はプロンプトで強めに指定してください。

しっぽヘアーは破綻しやすい構造の一つです。解決策は今のところ確認できていません。(追記。プロンプトに"ponytail"を追加すると改善の見込みがあると情報がありました。ありがとうございます。)

モデルやLoRAの強度によっては胸が大きくなったり、背や年齢が高くなったりするので、プロンプト・ネガティブプロンプトで自分の好みに調節してください。

初めてのLoRA公開なので、感想・不備などがありましたらコメントお願いします

items.name: Sengoku Nadeko (Monogatari)
items.description:
Lora model for Sengoku Nadeko from Monogatari series. Only tested it on weights 0.7-0.8 but it worked well there.

I'm quite happy with how nice this worked out because I included many outfits and they seems to all work quite well. The main phrase that you will use is sengoku nadeko. For a regular hairstyle do brown hair, bangs and for the hairstyle using hairband use brown hair, hairband. Model might still include bangs so you can put bangs in negative to avoid that.

For her iconic outdoor outfit use cabbie hat, jacket, jacket on shoulders, jeans, pink shirt, ribbon, belt pouch. Pouch is actually often not visible in artworks cause it's more on the back side so you can leave that part out if you don't want it.

For her casual indoor outfit use frilled skirt, pink camisole, white thighhighs, cardigan, open cardigan.

For her swimsuit just school swimsuit is enough.

And then if you want to make her medusa style replace all hairstyle and outfit words with white hair, snake hair, albino, red eyes, white dress. I noticed model still struggles with hair even remotely looking like snakes here so you might want to put more weight on that.

I know there are even more outfits and hairstyle I could have included but I think this is enough already.

This page serves as my depository for LORAs trained on the abyssal fleet girls from kantai collection, most of which I will train over time. I will not train all of them, as that is a tall order by itself and many of them either do not have enough images for decent training, or have designs that are just too wild for the AI to accurately grasp. However, I do plan to at least attmept the well-known ones alongside some personal choices (if possible). For any abyssal girls done already elsewhere on Civitai, those will likely be last on my list to do.

If it seems like I'm purposely not doing one you want, first of all, give me some time. Secondly, just leave a comment and I'll consider it in the future. Thirdly, make sure it's not because there's already another post featuring it.

Leave a like on this page to stay updated on future releases. Before downloading, be extra sure to check the "about this version" drop down, it's very likely I will have included information there regarding that specific lora.

Preview images may be from past versions! Do not expect full replication!

  • If some do not work, it is possible it was trained as a locon, for which you will need to download the appropriate extension.

  • Most LORAs should share the same "abyssal ship"/"shinkaisei-kan" tag in addition to the ship name and possibly shortened nickname (for easier prompting).

For the record, I have never played this game. I just think the enemy designs are cool and underrated/underappreciated, and admittedly know precious little about their actual lore.

items.name: Analog Diffusion Lora
items.description:
This is not a model I trained, it's seemingly disappeared from Civit, but I received a request to upload it by someone in a comment on one of my models. So any moderators for Civit, please just let me know if I need to remove it.

I honestly don't know much about the model, other than I always use 3 words when using it "Analog" "Depth of Field" "Portra 800 film". It was designed to give an analog film look to your images, with the added benefit of having precise control as a lora. I seem to remember these were the trigger words on the initial posting for the lora when it was up, and it always seemed to make the images look much more aesthetic.

UPDATE:

I was informed that this lora was extracted from a fully trained checkpoint with the same name "Analog Diffusion" by Wavymulder. Which you can find here!

https://civitai.com/models/1265/analog-diffusion

items.name: Carrie Fisher LoRA
items.description:
A Stable Diffusion LoRA profile based on Carrie Fisher, aka Princess Leia from Star Wars.

This is v.1 testing a new, quicker method I am experimenting with to create these profiles. V.2 will arrive in a day or two. Already giving great results!

Only using images of Carrie from the first movie trilogy, Obviously I only use high quality images but because of the time period this does like to kick out black and white images maybe 30% of the time, this can be controlled with your prompts.

It is generating really nice pictures already though, so please share your images!

Place it in "stable-diffusion-webui\extensions\sd-webui-additional-networks\models\lora" folder in Automatic1111 WebUI root folder.

Made using kohya-ss.

In txt2img, under "Additional Networks", select "Enable" and under Model 1 select "Carrie Fisher_v1" and assign a weight between 0.5-0.7 (the weight required can change depending on the checkpoint being used - feel free to experiment!). In the prompt text window use "Carrie Fisher_v1" within your prompt to generate images.

Embed has been trained on Stable Diffusion 1.5 model.

I Recommend the model https://civitai.com/models/4922/grapelikedreamfruit - Gives amazing realistic renders.
